LICENSE FOR THE VoxBlink DATASET

Description:
The VoxBlink dataset is an audio-visual dataset captured automatically from users who upload short videos on the YouTube platform. It comprises over 1.4M utterances from over 38K speakers. A clean version, termed VoxBlink-clean, contains 18k individuals and 1.02M utterances. Owing to its collection from diverse sources, VoxBlink inherently exhibits cross-age, cross-lingual, cross-channel, and cross-device attributes. As an audio-visual dataset, it has potential uses in a variety of applications. For more, please see https://voxblink.github.io. 

